In this seminar for Windows PKI you will learn how to implement and use a PKI in your enterprise.
Full Description:
In the seminar we will explain the technical fundamentals of a PKI (public key infrastructure) an the architecture of Certificate Services. You will learn the procedure of installing and configuring a Windows CA Server, the usage and customization of default Certificate Templates, Policy- and Exit-Modules and the integration of smart cards. One major subject are the different registration and enrollment methods. You will learn how to use the issued X.509 certificates with standard applications like Outlook, Acrobat or Internet Explorer and you will see how SmartCard Logon and VPN can be used. Furthermore, important organizational measures like PKI roles and authorizations and backup & recovery will be explained.
This seminar is intended for IT managers, system administrators and IT project managers.
Duration: 2 days

Description: Nearly all people who do not maintain good daily oral hygiene will develop gingivitis
Full Description: Nearly all people who do not maintain good daily oral hygiene will develop gingivitis. If left untreated, this bacterial gum infection can progress from gingivitis to periodontitis, which results in bone loss around your teeth. As the bone tissue is lost, the gum tissues detach from the teeth and form little pockets that provide an even better place for bacteria to live — where your brush and floss can't reach. As periodontal disease advances leading to more bone loss, tooth loss can result. This event will talk thru 1) Signs and Symptoms of Periodontal Disease and 2) Treatment Options.

The Cloud Native Computing Foundation’s flagship conference gathers leading technologists from leading open source and cloud native communities to further the education and advancement of cloud native computing.

Description: WCEF gathers entrepreneurs, crypto enthusiasts, and industry leaders to discuss the latest trends in the business and technological worlds.
Full Description:
The World Crypto Economic Forum (WCEF) is scheduled for June 2&3rd, 2022 in San Francisco and will gather over a hundred speakers and 2.000 attendees, entrepreneurs, crypto enthusiasts, and industry leaders for a discussion of the latest trends both in the business (Web3, DeFi, DAO, NFT, Meta, IDO, etc.) and technological worlds (everything blockchain).
It was just announced that Michael Arrington – Founder of TechCrunch, Crunchbase, and XRP Capital, named as one of Time Magazine’s 100 most influential people – will perform at the event. Another keynote speaker is Dr. Chandra Duggirala, Co-Founder and CEO of Portal, a decentralized financial platform that blends Bitcoin and Layer 2. Starting out as a doctor, Chandra found his calling through entrepreneurship. He is passionate about reducing real barriers to entrepreneurship and decentralizing finance and opportunity.
A number of notable entrepreneurs and blockchain professionals are also expected to attend, such as Vinny Lingham (Waitroom/Civic Technologies), Jonathan Nelson (HF.Capital), Nathalie Kara (Propy), Lori Corpuz (@ NFT OASIS), Miko Matsumura (Gumi Cryptos Capital), Greg Osuri (Akash Network), William Bear (Nearverse) and others. The participants will cover various aspects of the digital economy – from blockchain technology to new economic models based on tokens.
The WCEF will also include lightning talks, networking sessions with top executives, a token pitch, and a hackathon.

Description: Sources trusted by investors, shareholders, and stakeholders all agree that climate change is a global emergency.
Full Description:
Sources trusted by investors, shareholders, and stakeholders all agree that climate change is a global emergency. Regardless of the cause, the world needs to take immediate and ambitious climate actions to mitigate future disaster. Climate governance entails more than just embedding climate transition into an organization’s strategy. Very soon, regulations will require full disclosures and rigorous metrics. Is your board prepared?
Businesses across industries are feeling the pressure coming from multiple sources. The SEC climate rule may require broad emissions disclosures, and investors are imploring boards to act. Stakeholders are insisting that climate transition plans are part of corporate agendas, while competitors are developing new solutions and products and reframing their strategies.

Description: Monthly Barometer Summit of Minds Chamonix 2021
Full Description:
It is our great pleasure to invite you to the next edition of the Chamonix MB Summit of Minds (17-19 September 2021). After more than a year of suspended animation, our enthusiasm to bring our community back together is as vibrant as ever.
Read the draft programme of sessions & experiential activities, as well as additional information concerning accommodation in Chamonix and travel.
True to its long-standing philosophy, the Summit will be an ideas fair articulated around two main threads:
Key macro issues – economics, geopolitics, society, environment and tech: how they are likely to evolve in the coming years and how they’ll impact your investment and business decisions.
Wellness & wellbeing: their critical relevance for improving your decision making both, personal and professional.
This year, natural capital (nature as a productive asset) – a theme at the intersection of the two threads – will be a core component of our programme. This is reflected in the good4nature prize that will be awarded for the first time in Chamonix this year.

Event Name: Ax-1 Mission Launching from Kennedy Space Center
Description: The launch of Axiom Space's first all-private astronaut crew to the International Space Station
Full Description:
The turning of chapters in the human story has been marked by inflection points, dividing the before irrevocably from the after. Axiom provides missions to Earth’s orbit because the dawn of true private spaceflight is the next in that line of moments. Only into the expanse outside our atmosphere can the species step out of the cradle.
And it all begins with this multinational crew. This groundbreaking mission. The humanitarian leaders flying Ax-1 are the first in a new class of pioneers stepping forth to lay the groundwork for a full realization of Low Earth Orbit’s possibilities – in service of all on Earth and all who will follow them beyond it.
The team includes Michael Alegria-Lopez, Mark Pathy, Eytan Stibbe and Larry Connor.

Event Name: How AI is Being Developed at OPM for Cybersecurity Threats
Description: October 2022 AI in Government Featured Presentation
Full Description:
Join featured Melvin Brown II, Deputy Chief Information Officer in the U.S. Office of Personnel Management and his presentation ‘How AI is Being Developed at OPM for Cybersecurity Threats’.
The evolution of cloud computing and artificial intelligence are growing in parallel, and the complexity of the cloud is driving the need for AI. In addition, the complexity of AI is also creating the need for it to work better in the cloud environment with efficiency, transparency and control.
Organizations are taking a more data-driven approach, where artificial intelligence can be used to detect and proactively provide alerts on weaknesses and vulnerabilities both that are being exploited right now, or that might be exploited in the future. This is being done by analyzing data coming in and out of protected endpoints, both detecting threats based on known behavior, and spotting yet known threats based on predictive analytics. In this session we will be examining a use case for AI in action to prevent potential unauthorized access and the benefits of AI for cloud security services that include:
• Identification of threats that would otherwise go undetected.
• Automatization of the process of responding to threats.
• Improvement of the efficiency of security operations.
• Ability to reduce the cost of security operations.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A with Melvin! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website.

Data science is transforming business and generating new value across the organization. Data science still often requires dedicated technology and sophisticated teams to execute successfully. As departments work to address today's wide range of competitive, regulatory, and operational challenges, it is easy to overlook a critical issue that many of their most complex challenges have in common: nearly all of them either are rooted in or exacerbated by ML tooling, ML Model governance issues (Bias and fairness), and training, including shortcomings in data access, data quality, or both. Data Science center of excellence (CoE) can be a centralized group that centers on a discipline's vision, governance, technique, and framework. This is especially helpful for data science because of the specialty abilities and innovation the discipline requires. Data Science center of excellence (CoE) can improve efficiency and stability in maintaining and delivering business-critical data improved decision-making through fairness and unbiased models with adequate compliance and regulatory needs.

Event Name: How to Avoid AI Project Failure
Description: October 2022 Cognilytica AI Failures Webinar 'How to Avoid AI Project Failure'
Full Description:
Cognilytica is excited to host Managing Partners Kathleen Walch and Ron Schmelzer and their presentation ‘How to Avoid AI Project Failure’ on Wednesday, October 19, 2022 at 1 PM ET!
Artificial intelligence and advanced data projects are gaining rapid traction. However, with all this interest and hype in AI, only a small percentage of AI projects are actually seeing success. Why are so many AI projects failing when they don’t need to? With all the resources, great technology, and skilled talent put towards building AI projects, we shouldn’t be seeing so much AI project failure, but up to 80% of AI projects are not being completed successfully or achieving critical success measures. Clearly it’s not a technology or people problem, so what could be the main issues holding back AI project success?
Leveraging experience with thousands of AI projects and experience through best-practices approaches to AI, Cognilytica shares in this webinar the most common reasons for AI project failures and the insights to be learned from those failures. In this webinar we will discuss common reasons we see AI projects fail, the risk of overpromising and underdelivering on AI capabilities, methodologies and processes that can guarantee a higher rate of success, and how to avoid the common traps and pitfalls that usually beset AI projects.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A at the end! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica website.

Event Name: Intro to CPMAI Methodology for Project and Product Managers

Full Description:
Cognilytica is excited to host Kathleen Walch and Ron Schmelzer, Managing Partners at Cognilytica and their presentation ‘Intro to CPMAI Methodology for Project and Product Managers’ on Wednesday, October 19, 2022 at 1 PM ET!
Far too often, agencies, organizations, and consulting firms are running data and AI projects without taking the right steps to ensure their success. Agile and iterative approaches have become adopted best practices for application development projects, but why don’t we have something similar when it comes to advanced analytics, big data, and AI projects? Without using best-practices approaches that standardize steps for data preparation, data identification, and data protection, it’s hard to achieve the success you’re expecting, wasting money and resources, leading to failure.
This session will walk through the Cognitive Project Management for AI (CPMAI) methodology to provide the foundation needed for project success, especially as you incorporate advanced analytics and AI projects. The CPMAI methodology is the established best practice for AI & ML projects, and increasingly will be demanded by organizations and agencies that plan to develop, procure, and deliver AI and advanced analytics projects. This session will provide real world examples of how CPMAI methodology allows individuals to gain the skills needed for AI project success.

Event Name: Hekka launch new Swimwear collection on Uplive on 2022 Japan Swim Week
Regions: Asia-Pacific (APAC), Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), Southeast Asia
Description: Hekka and Uplive To Feature Jaw-dropping Looks on 2022 Japan Swim Week.
Full Description:
JAPAN, June 29th, 2022, Hekka and Uplive are getting ready to make one more big online show together this July 1-7, 2022, over the Japan Swim Week. Over seven days, Hekka will be the main outfit sponsor of Uplive's livestreaming audition show for the Japanese audience, following a highly successful tie-up during New York Fashion Week. This year’s event will celebrate the return of travel and vacation breaks, featuring Hekka's new swimwear capsule collection, "Style de Vie", a 30-piece capsule collection of swimwear. 
Alongside its partner brand, Uplive, the leading global live video platform launched by Asia Innovations Group (AIG), the event will stage Japan's most famous Uplive hosts that will be featuring Hekka outfits, in its effort to promote both brands to the Japanese audience, as the Japan Swim Week becomes the focal point of the fashion world. 
It marks the second time Hekka and Uplive have collaborated this year following the success of NYFW 2022. Utilising Hekka’s unique “real time fashion” platform and Uplive's global reach, the brand expects to greatly increase awareness and user take up. It is projected that at least 10,000 media impressions across social channels for Hekka and Uplive will be generated, creating quality publicity that will continue to grow the innovative cooperation between the sister companies. The innovation in cooperation illustrates their parent group, AIG’s mission “to enrich people's lives worldwide through innovative and enjoyable live social products, which foster meaningful human connection”.
For Hekka, the inclusiveness to celebrate style for every woman, is core to the collection, whilst continuing to showcase some of the hottest looks across affordable designer swimwear. The "Style de Vie" range is a 30-piece lifestyle capsule collection of swimwear, apparel and accessories handpicked and inspired by modern trends, where 'be comfortable with your own style' is the goal and inspires owners every time they wear a piece from the collection. Included in the collection will be a range of the most popular selling bikinis and one pieces, as well as patterned and two-tone styles that will meet the runway for the very first time. 
“The collection we are bringing to Japan Swim Week this year is just a snapshot of what Hekka have to offer. We want to enable all our customers to be their true self and unleash an inner confidence inside of them” said Laure-Cecile Lafond-Fenonjoie, CMO of Hekka. “Our choice of clothing can activate a sense of amazingness within us, and through our ranges of swimwear and resort wear, we want everyone to bask in the distinct energy that fashion can provide.”
About Hekka
Founded in Singapore, Hekka is an international online marketplace that features a broad range of products and is emerging as a lifestyle shopping platform that brings products at a fair price. Together with its global audience, Hekka cherishes and celebrates everyday moments through its capability to create an inclusive, cross-border and seamless shopping experience for all. Leveraging latest mobile technology and following emerging trends, Hekka stands as a reminder that living life while celebrating simple everyday pleasures is a great way to achieve life’s fulfillment. Launched by Asia Innovations Group (AIG), a leading live social company with more than 500 million registered users in over 150 regions worldwide, Hekka consists of an international team and partners across Europe, the USA, and India. For more information, visit hekka.com and follow @hekkaofficial on all social platforms.
About AIG
Asia Innovations Group (AIG) is a leading live social company with more than 500 million registered users located in over 150 regions worldwide. It has built a comprehensive and diverse portfolio as it seeks to achieve its mission of enriching people's lives worldwide through innovative and enjoyable live social products, which foster meaningful human connection. AIG's portfolio includes leading apps such as Uplive, the global live video platform, CuteU and Lamour, leading dating apps in global emerging markets, as well as other fast-growing voice and game based live social apps. Its e-commerce platform, Hekka Fashion, offers an online shopping experience that brings accessible fashion to users and provides a host of opportunities for collaboration across AIG products. AIG operates in eighteen offices around the globe that bring deep local market knowledge across all major emerging markets. Combined with cutting-edge technology and a scalable global infrastructure, AIG is bringing the most exciting social product experiences to users across emerging markets.

Event Name: Case Complexity Analysis: Using Advanced Analytics to Understand Complex Problems
Description: August 2022 Enterprise Data & AI Event featuring Guidehouse
Full Description:
Enterprise Data & AI is hosting guest speaker Dr. Harold Walbert, Solutions Data Analytics Manager at Guidehouse  and his presentation "Case Complexity Analysis: Using Advanced Analytics to Understand Complex Problems" on Thursday, August 18, 2022 from 12 PM - 1 PM ET!
A problem can be solved or a question answered in many ways, but some ways may be better than others. The question of how hard a problem is to solve is something that scientists, researchers, computer scientists, governments and businesses have all thought about for a long time. These different groups work in different domains and are concerned with different questions of interest but an underlying need to categorize questions into categories is a need that unites them all. You may have a problem you want to solve, like sorting a list from highest to lowest or understanding which applications for a program will take the longest to adjudicate. Some of the questions (especially in the computational arena) don’t necessarily have a human interaction or social complexity aspect to them. Other questions (like those primarily asked in business and governmental contexts) are inescapably tied to issues around human behavior and the added complexity that it brings. Using advanced analytics we can begin to understand these problems better and position ourselves in ways that lead to better outcomes. 
Join this webinar to learn how Guidehouse achieves the best performance possible given these complicated problems using Case Complexity Analysis. Be sure to stick around for Q&A with Harold! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica website: https://www.cognilytica.com/CLNzAyNjh8MTg

Event Name: Intro to CPMAI Certification by Cognilytica
Description: September 2022 Intro to CPMAI Certification Event by Cognilytica
Full Description:
Cognilytica is hosting Kathleen Walch and Ron Schmelzer, Managing Partners at Cognilytica and their presentation ‘Intro to CPMAI Certification’ on Tuesday, September 6, 2022 at 11:30 AM ET!
Far too often, agencies, organizations, and consulting firms are running data and AI projects without taking the right steps to ensure their success. Agile and iterative approaches have become adopted best practices for application development projects, but why don’t we have something similar when it comes to advanced analytics, big data, and AI projects? Without using best-practices approaches that standardize steps for data preparation, data identification, and data protection, it’s hard to achieve the success you’re expecting, wasting money and resources, leading to failure.
This session will walk through the Cognitive Project Management for AI (CPMAI) methodology to provide the foundation needed for project success, especially as you incorporate advanced analytics and AI projects. The CPMAI methodology is the established best practice for AI & ML projects, and increasingly will be demanded by organizations and agencies that plan to develop, procure, and deliver AI and advanced analytics projects. This session will provide real world examples of how CPMAI methodology allows individuals to gain the skills needed for AI project success.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A at the end! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica website: https://www.cognilytica.com/CLNzAyMzJ8MTg

Event Name: Hekka and Uplive To Feature Jaw-dropping Looks on 2022 Miami Swim Week Runway
Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Description: Hekka and Uplive To Feature Jaw-dropping Looks on 2022 Miami Swim Week Runway.
Full Description:
Hekka and Uplive are getting ready to make a big splash this July 14-17, 2022, in Miami South Beach over Miami Swim Week 2022. Over four days, Hekka will join more than 200 leading brands to showcase new designs and debut 2023 collections during the world's largest swimwear and beach fashion event. This year's event will celebrate the return of travel and vacation breaks, moving forward from the covid-19 era, as designers from over 70 countries attend the show. Meanwhile, pioneering technologies will be blended with fashion including a virtual swimwear Metaverse. Over 20,000 industry stakeholders including retail platforms, media, designers, bloggers and celebrities will descend on iconic locations such as Miami South Beach attending a week full of runway shows, VIP parties, and exclusive events. Miami Swim Week is expected to reach more than 1.6 billion impressions across social channels. 
On heel of Hekka's stellar debut at New York Fashion Week earlier this year, Hekka will launch at Miami Swim Week 2022 "Style de Vie", a 30-piece capsule collection of swimwear for the first time. Alongside its partner brand, Uplive, the leading global live video platform launched by Asia Innovations Group (AIG), they will extend Hekka's designs and Uplive's social platform to new audiences, as Miami Swim Week becomes the focal point of the fashion world.
It marks the second time Hekka and Uplive have collaborated this year following the success of NYFW 2022. Utilising Hekka's unique "real time fashion" platform and Uplive's global reach, the brand expects to greatly increase awareness and user take up. It is projected that at least 2 million media impressions for Hekka and Uplive will be generated, creating quality publicity that will continue to grow the innovative cooperation between the sister companies. The innovation in cooperation illustrates their parent group, AIG's mission "to enrich people's lives worldwide through innovative and enjoyable live social products, which foster meaningful human connection".
For Hekka, the inclusiveness to celebrate style for every woman, is core to the collection, whilst continuing to showcase some of the hottest looks across affordable designer swimwear. The "Style de Vie" range is a 30-piece lifestyle capsule collection of swimwear, apparel and accessories handpicked and inspired by modern trends, where 'be comfortable with your own style' is the goal and inspires owners every time they wear a piece from the collection. Included in the collection will be a range of the most popular selling bikinis and one pieces, as well as patterned and two-tone styles that will meet the runway for the very first time. 
"The collection we are bringing to Miami Swim Week this year is just a snapshot of what Hekka have to offer. We want to enable all our customers to be their true self and unleash an inner confidence inside of them" said Laure-Cecile Lafond-Fenonjoie, CMO of Hekka. "Our choice of clothing can activate a sense of amazingness within us, and through our ranges of swimwear and resort wear, we want everyone to bask in the distinct energy that fashion can provide."
About Hekka
Founded in Singapore, Hekka is an international online marketplace that features a broad range of products and is emerging as a lifestyle shopping platform that brings products at a fair price. Together with its global audience, Hekka cherishes and celebrates everyday moments through its capability to create an inclusive, cross-border and seamless shopping experience for all. Leveraging latest mobile technology and following emerging trends, Hekka stands as a reminder that living life while celebrating simple everyday pleasures is a great way to achieve life's fulfillment. Launched by Asia Innovations Group (AIG), a leading live social company with more than 500 million registered users in over 150 regions worldwide, Hekka consists of an international team and partners across Europe, the USA, and India. For more information, visit hekka.com and follow @hekkaofficial on all social platforms.
About AIG
Asia Innovations Group (AIG) is a leading live social company with more than 500 million registered users located in over 150 regions worldwide. It has built a comprehensive and diverse portfolio as it seeks to achieve its mission of enriching people's lives worldwide through innovative and enjoyable live social products, which foster meaningful human connection. AIG's portfolio includes leading apps such as Uplive, the global live video platform, CuteU and Lamour, leading dating apps in global emerging markets, as well as other fast-growing voice and game based live social apps. Full Description:
AI in Government is hosting guest speaker Jeremy Golant, Government Solutions Consultant at Coursera presenting ‘Driving Data Literacy in the Public Sector’ on Wednesday, August 10, 2022 from 12 PM - 1 PM ET! 
As data becomes more seamlessly integrated within decision-making processes, public sector agencies must ensure individuals across the workforce can read, work with, and question data in the context of their role. Data literacy shouldn’t be mistaken for technical literacy, and it doesn’t necessarily include the skills and knowledge needed by a data scientist. Event Name: What is Engineering Education in Germany?
Description: Live classes, video lectures and customized study plans. Daily Live Classes Doubt clarification.
Full Description:
Engineers not only innovate new products in the market but they also manage safety for their products. Awareness of environment safety is now an important part of qualifications of engineering. With the increase in the population, updation of new technology, globalization of businesses, and industrialization, these all are challenges the world of engineering. A long tradition of providing Engineering in Germany education to national and international applicants are same. 
You will get a lot of advantages of for high quality education provided by Germany without any tuition fees. The engineering degree of Germany is worldwide recognized and it will benefit in getting higher salary in Future.
Reasons for study Engineering in Germany?
1. There is no tuition fee for German program at state universities
2. A lot of job options are available for Engineering in Germany
3. Research and collaboration with various industries 
4. A degree that is worldwide recognized
5. Highest quality of education from top-class universities in Germany
There are 400+ universities in Germany in-house and some universities outside the state. Almost of the universities in Germany are funded by the state, that means there is no tuition fee.
Famous Engineering programs in Germany
There are a lot of programs available for studying Engineering in Germany. These programs are listed below :-
1. Automobile Engineering
2. Mechatronics
3. Industrial Engineering
4. Information Technology
5. Civil Engineering
6. Electrical Engineering
7. Computer science/Engineering
8. Mechanical Engineering
Pathways for study Engineering in Germany
Applicants who have completed their 12 years of school must complete 1 year preparatory course from their schools. The preparatory course is for 1 year and it ends with examination called Assessment Test.
Applicants who have completed the A- level must pass literature subject examination. If a student has passed the literature examination then he or she can study bachelor's degree of Engineering in Germany in English medium. Although there are very few subjects available in English medium. For studying in German medium, applicant must pass B-1 level examination.
It takes nearly 4-5 years for completion of Engineering in Germany in German medium. It consists of the time required for learning German and foundation course.
How can you start your preparation for studies Engineering in Germany?
One of the best ways to start your preparation for studying in Germany is to get enrolled for German language course. If you have completed 12th examination and waiting for results, then it is the best time to join German course till your results are out.

Event Name: All about vocational training in Germany
Description: Live classes with top vocational trainers, video lectures, mock tests, and customized study plans. Daily Live Classes Doubt clarification.
Full Description:
One of the best ways for your training in Germany is in pursuance of dual vocational training programme. These programmes provides a lot of benefits on on-the-job-training and practical experience of work also. Vocational training in Germany normally last for 2-3 years and it includes both theoretical as well as practical training. You will obtain theoretical knowledge of 1-2 days a week from vocational schools and rest of the time at a company in which you will acquired practical knowledge. For example, what your company were doing work, how to operate a machinery, and many more.
Vocational training in Germany and What amount they will pay
Students who pursuing vocational training in Germany receives a monthly salary from the company which they were work for. On an average, a student may receive a gross income of nearly €987.00. It is totally depending upon the occupation and the region you will work. The salary may be higher and lower from this amount. This amount will increase as you will complete with each year of training. Some amount of the salary will be deducted for social security contribution.
Stages of dual vocational training in Germany
Dual vocational training in Germany starts from 1st of August or 1st of September every year. These training includes both on-the-job-training in a company and theoretical classes at vocational schools. These classes include German, English, and social studies. Nearly 2/3rd of the classes particularly focus on the subjects that are most important for your future work. While your training programme is going on, you are entitled to take leave of minimum 24 business days or 4 weeks annually. 
You will get full support from your teachers, instructors, and colleagues you require during your completion of programme. After the first half of the training programme you will take an examination to evaluate what you have learned in your class and how you will apply your knowledge in a company. Your exams will be held in German itself, as it is a rule of Germany. If you will pass in your exams, you will get a lot of opportunities in future and you will start a successful career in Germany. 
International attractiveness for excellent training
The main advantage of training is that they obtain market related training which is continuously growing to the latest innovation of the digital era. There is a developing awareness across Europe and globally that high-quality work based vocational training in Germany is important for competitiveness. Demand from different companies for cooperation with Germany remains at high standard. The development of excellent vocational training and education is the principle of bilateral cooperation under the Berlin memorandum of December 2013. 
Conclusion
Vocational training in Germany is a dual aspect where you can learn training in the classroom and in practical life. You can earn while learning. After you Finished your apprenticeship, you can get the better job opportunities in Germany regardless where is your citizenship. If you are interested in doing this course, then you can visit us at migr8.in

Description: International Cybersecurity Conference
Full Description:
Digital Europe was initially designed to serve the development of the Single Market. But recently, sovereignty and cybersecurity have become two of the Commission’s objectives in a strategic context marked by the domination of the two digital superpowers, the United States and China. Yet Europe does not lack assets. It still lacked a unified and ambitious discourse, followed by effective action sustained over time. In March 2021, the European Commission showed the way by launching its “Digital Decade” programme. Cybersecurity has an essential place in this strategy. It is both its cornerstone and spearhead.
The operational response is based on an industrial foundation that guarantees strategic autonomy. After defining demanding standards for security and personal data protection, Europe must create the conditions for ecosystems to develop, whether in cloud computing, artificial intelligence, quantum computing, or semiconductors. The ways and means of cybersecurity call for a political stance. Europe must equip itself with the diplomatic tools that will enable it to “persuade”—if not “dissuade”—potential adversaries and to assert its interests and its vision of a sustainable digital world, centered on human beings and based on shared values.
After the time for reflection, the time for pragmatism and action has come! The many legislative projects (NIS2, cyber resilience, e-evidence, product security, DMA, DSA, semiconductors, etc.) will only bear fruit if they are accompanied by a rapid increase in capabilities (operational, technological, military, diplomatic, industrial, etc.) contributing to cyber security. But the first condition is the mobilisation of talents and skills. At a time when historical alliances are weakening or disintegrating, the question can be summed up as follows: “to be or not to be European”. Europe kicks off!
The FIC 2022 will be one of the events of the French Presidency of the Council of the European Union on digital security and trust issues.
Industry Group: Information Technology, Privacy and Security, Software

Event Name: Model Maintenance: Hidden Costs of Data Science
Description: August 2022 Enteprise Data & AI Featured Speaker from Swiss Re
Full Description:
Join the August 2022 Enterprise Data & AI featured guest speaker Jerry Gupta, Senior Vice President, Personal and Commercial Insurance Research and Development at Swiss Re and his presentation ‘Model Maintenance: Hidden Costs of Data Science’ on Thursday, August 4, 2022 from 11:30 AM - 1 PM ET!
Data Analytics is considered the fourth phase of industrialization. Not surprisingly, organizations are rushing to build up and accelerate their data science capabilities. While robustness of data, and availability of talent remain their primary concerns, one of the hidden failure modes is model maintenance. MIT Sloan Tech Review estimates that these costs can add up to several times the cost of model development over the lifecycle of the model. Yet majority of companies continue to underestimate both the costs and complexity associated with model maintenance. This results in poor ROI, but more importantly, model maintenance is a weight around the ankles of data science teams that results in reduced productivity and attrition.
Join this interactive session to learn the hidden costs of data science in model maintenance and stick around till the end for Q&A with Jerry! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website.

Ausbildung in Germany
 
On the off chance that you just have an "Abitur" or the identical capability (12th pass), you'll focus on double-track professional preparation in Germany. Double track preparation includes both hypothetical and down-to-earth parts.
Let's speak about what's Ausbildung in Germany.
AUSBILDUNG could be a type of education or apprenticeship where a student attends school and works simultaneously. the student gains both theoretical and practical knowledge at the identical time. it's a profession-related education that is leading you towards a certain job. you'll be able to find Ausbildung for pretty much anything.
Duration of Ausbildung Program in Germany
Normally, the Ausbildung program goes on for 3-4 years, yet assuming your grades are great in light of your exhibition within the organization and professional preparation school, then this era will decrease. 
In any case, it's no huge effect, because the hour of three years may be decreased to 2.5 years, so it hardly matters.
The period typically relies upon different elements like which organization you're working for, which office you're relegated to, and from which professional preparation school you're examining.
In any case, there's something significant you gravely expect to be qualified for the Ausbildung program, which is capable of the High German.
Language Requirement For Ausbildung In Germany
You can apply for an apprenticeship in Germany if you're an overseas national and you have got German as your natural language. If you're not, you'll be able to still apply for this program. you simply must ensure you're fluent in the German language.
You also can apply for an Ausbildung if you have got no formal education but have an interest in technical fields. In almost every field of study, you'll apply for this program. It will be a dual education or education.
 
What Is vocational education In Germany?
Vocational training prepares you for an occupation or work that needs a special set of skills, like an artisan, tradesperson, technician, craftsman, or electrician. this may include classroom teaching, practical training, or a mixture of the 2. However, education takes place outside the formal education system to realize practical knowledge and frequently ends up in a vocational qualification certificate or diploma. you'll directly receive vocational education as an apprentice from an experienced employer irrespective of whether you have got a proper qualification or not.
Importance Of vocational education In Germany 
Following are some reasons for vocational education in Germany:-
Vocational training allows you to seek out a high-paying job or career quickly after completing the programme.
It helps you in improving your work efficiency and being more productive in your job.
Vocational training provides skilled and trained workers to the market and industry.
Vocational training provides employment opportunities in small cities and towns, thereby preventing the population from migrating to big cities.
After completing the vocational education, you may receive a certificate issued by an independent organization, proving that your skills and position are better than applicants without formal training.
What is new in education in Germany?
Germany offers a dual vocational education programme that has opportunities for on-the-job training and acquiring practical work experience. The duration of dual vocational education courses is around two to a few years, where you're given both theoretical and practical knowledge. A student is required to spend the initial few weeks with the training school to find out theoretical knowledge required for the work, after which the student is shipped to the assigned company for practical experience and practice. the opposite way of delivering the programme may be a day or two spent within the classroom of the participating training center and therefore the remaining days of the week on the work placement.
These are some following reasons why you must pursue vocational education in Germany instead of the other country.
Vocational training courses may be your ticket to a permanent career within the German job market. Approximately two-thirds of apprentices have found permanent positions within the company after completing vocational education. After completing the program, you may obtain an entire professional qualification from the institute and earn an honest income. every one of the advantages of working with an identical training company is that you simply already know your company, your work, and your colleagues, which can surely benefit you.
The demand for vocational trainees is incredibly high in Germany. Various companies and organizations in Germany are trying to find vocational trainees, so there are high chances to secure employment after vocational education qualification.

Full Description:
Artificial intelligence and advanced data projects are gaining rapid traction. However, with all this interest and hype in AI, only a small percentage of AI projects are actually seeing success. Why are so many AI projects failing when they don’t need to? With all the resources, great technology, and skilled talent put towards building AI projects, we shouldn’t be seeing so much AI project failure, but up to 80% of AI projects are not being completed successfully or achieving critical success measures. Clearly it’s not a technology or people problem, so what could be the main issues holding back AI project success?
Leveraging experience with thousands of AI projects and experience through best-practices approaches to AI, Cognilytica shares in this webinar the most common reasons for AI project failures and the insights to be learned from those failures. In this webinar we will discuss common reasons we see AI projects fail, the risk of overpromising and underdelivering on AI capabilities, methodologies and processes that can guarantee a higher rate of success, and how to avoid the common traps and pitfalls that usually beset AI projects.

Event Name: The Difficulties and Limitations of Implementing AI at the CFTC and Beyond
Description: August 2022 AI in Government Feature Presentation
Full Description:
Most institutions necessarily institute artificial intelligence (AI) to solve individual use cases in their enterprise, a form of “first-generation AI”. A chess program, speech recognition, an algorithm to rapidly buy and sell financial products. These are straightforward applications of structured data problems. One of the chief difficulties is in getting understanding in the enterprise beyond these structured data cases, particularly in the domain of limited budgets. Once the “first generation AI” is implemented, successfully or not, the next step is more lateral movement – development of more standalone cases, rather than layering and refactoring to produce additional complexity, the neural nets and deep learning AI problem sets. Join this interactive session to learn some of the difficulties associated with implementing AI as well as the difficulties moving from “first generation” to “second generation” AI in order to achieve business process improvement by modifying data architecture to reflect how data is actually used.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A with Dr. Roust! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website: https://www.cognilytica.com/CLNjc0ODR8MTg

Smart Hospital: cloud and AI solutions for logistics management, maintenance and procedural processes of hospital buildings and procurement processes (e.g., cold chain).
Training and Education: advanced support for specialists also based on AR/VR solutions for purposes eg. of exercise, simulation and support of interventions, for the improvement of skills and operational training.
Sustainability:
Application solutions, based on big data analytics and artificial intelligence, that help companies achieve sustainability goals, such as reducing dependence on fossil fuels, reducing CO2 emissions, measuring environmental impact, minimizing energy consumption, reduce waste and methodologies to preserve ecosystems and territories.
Application solutions, based on big data analytics and artificial intelligence, to support sustainable mobility, to reduce CO2 emissions due to the movement of things and/or people, whether it is road transport, sea transport and/or airplane.
CaaS (Container as a Service):
In the context of Cloud transformation, the most advanced and efficient choice is a container-based and microservices-oriented solution, highly innovative cloud-based solutions are sought that can support the operation, management, and maintenance of a MATCH-like architecture, based on Micro-services, API-first, Cloud-native and Headless.
Eligibility Criteria
Participants to the Challenge may be national and international companies, small and medium-size enterprises, and scaleups that meet all the following eligibility criteria:
must have been established for at least 1 year up to a maximum of 15 years;
2021 revenue amounting to € 50.000,00 or higher, or with more than € 500.000,00 received in funding;
introducing an innovative digital project that leverages on the company’s own digital products or services and that has a level of technological readiness greater than 6 as defined in accordance with the previsions contained in the Technology Readiness Level Annex (“Exhibit 1”).
Proposals evaluation and Award
The challenge will remain open from March 1 st to March 31 st, 2022.
For any technical or organizational need, the Organization reserves the right to change the start and closing date of the challenge, informing the Applicants.
Proposals will be evaluated by a jury composed of TIM and Noovle managers and external experts who will identify the best projects.
The Jury will evaluate the Proposals submitted by the Candidates at its sole and unquestionable discretion, according to the evaluation criteria set out in the Rules and Regulations.
Applicants must accept the of the Rules and Regulations of the Challenge and the related information, by checking the specific section on the website and declaring that they have read the privacy policy.
The award ceremony will take place in May during the dedicated event with the participation of Google Cloud.
The winning proposals will have the opportunity to negotiate a collaboration agreement with Noovle (Article 5 of the Rules and Regulations).

Event Name: Measuring Semantic SEO Results Using Google Data Studio, GA and GSC – Kalicube Tuesdays with Alex Silva and David Riccitelli
Description: Alex Silva and David Riccitelli and Jason Barnard will talk about measuring semantic SEO results using Google Data Studio, GA and GSC.
Full Description:
Wordlift Monthly Roundtable (August 2022)
Because SEO has a historical focus on keywords, when you are doing semantic SEO and bringing results, you will know that there is confusion and misunderstandings right down the line. But what if we could track, measure and demonstrate the effect and value of semantic SEO? Problem solved! During the webinar, Alex Silva and David Riccitelli will show how you can use Google Data Studio to combine and reformulate the data from Google Analytics and Google Search Console to demonstrate clearly the value it brings to your overall SEO strategy.
The webinar will be split into five parts:
– Quick overview of Semantic SEO and its application to a website (10 minutes)
– Some examples of concrete results achieved in terms of visibility and traffic (10 minutes)
– How to easily import and interpret Google Analytics and Search Console data using entities in Google Data Studio (15 minutes)
– How to best apply this game changing approach to get (and keep) the stakeholders onboard (15 minutes)
– Audience questions answered by Alex Silva and David Riccitelli (10 minutes)
Join Jason Barnard, Alex Silva and David Riccitelli to learn why semantic SEO is the future, what you can do to easily implement a semantic SEO strategy and (most importantly) how you can demonstrate the value and rewards to the stakeholders with the pursestrings.
Organised by Kalicube in partnership with Wordlift.
Part of the Kalicube Tuesdays series.

Event Name: The Top Reasons for AI Project Failure - and What you can Do about it
Description: July 2022 AI Failures Series by Cognilytica
Full Description:
Cognilytica is hosting Kathleen Walch and Ron Schmelzer, Managing Partners at Cognilytica and their presentation ‘The Top Reasons for AI Project Failure - and What you can Do about it’ on Tuesday, July 19, 2022 at 10 AM ET!
Artificial intelligence and advanced data projects are gaining rapid traction. However, with all this interest and hype in AI, only a small percentage of AI projects are actually seeing success. Why are so many AI projects failing when they don’t need to? With all the resources, great technology, and skilled talent put towards building AI projects, we shouldn’t be seeing so much AI project failure, but up to 80% of AI projects are not being completed successfully or achieving critical success measures. Clearly it’s not a technology or people problem, so what could be the main issues holding back AI project success?
 Leveraging experience with thousands of AI projects and experience through best-practices approaches to AI, Cognilytica shares in this webinar the most common reasons for AI project failures and the insights to be learned from those failures. In this webinar we will discuss common reasons we see AI projects fail, the risk of overpromising and underdelivering on AI capabilities, methodologies and processes that can guarantee a higher rate of success, and how to avoid the common traps and pitfalls that usually beset AI projects.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A at the end! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website: https://www.cognilytica.com/CLNjk2MzF8MTg

Event Name: Intro to CPMAI Methodology for Project Managers
Description: July 2022 Intro to CPMAI for Project Managers
Full Description:
Cognilytica is hosting Kathleen Walch and Ron Schmelzer, Managing Partners at Cognilytica and their presentation ‘Intro to CPMAI Methodology for Project Managers’ on Tuesday, July 5, 2022 at 10 AM ET!
Far too often, agencies, organizations, and consulting firms are running data and AI projects without taking the right steps to ensure their success. Agile and iterative approaches have become adopted best practices for application development projects, but why don’t we have something similar when it comes to advanced analytics, big data, and AI projects? Without using best-practices approaches that standardize steps for data preparation, data identification, and data protection, it’s hard to achieve the success you’re expecting, wasting money and resources, leading to failure.
This session will walk through the Cognitive Project Management for AI (CPMAI) methodology to provide the foundation needed for project success, especially as you incorporate advanced analytics and AI projects. The CPMAI methodology is the established best practice for AI & ML projects, and increasingly will be demanded by organizations and agencies that plan to develop, procure, and deliver AI and advanced analytics projects. This session will provide real world examples of how CPMAI methodology allows individuals to gain the skills needed for AI project success.

Full Description:
The June 2022 AI in Government event featured guest speaker is Dr. Susan Gregurick, Associate Director of Data Science at the National Institutes of Health and her presentation ‘AI at the NIH: Opportunities to Improve Biomedical Research and Human Health’ 
In biomedical and clinical research, AI has the potential to improve health and healthcare systems that will result in positive patient health outcomes. The NIH has recently developed several initiatives and programs to develop and enhance AI for biomedical research and to improve health outcomes for all of our citizens. This talk highlights NIH’s efforts in creating AI-ready data, developing ethical frameworks for the use of AI technologies in biomedicine, training new investigators at the interface of AI sciences and biomedical sciences, and utilizing AI to advance health equity. The talk will also highlight unmet challenges for the research community to consider. If you’re leading or managing an AI, data, or automation team, you should attend to find out more about how NIH is managing their data efforts, considering ethical frameworks, and other critical factors for running AI projects.

Event Name: Where Do Branded Searches on Google Come From? - Kalicube Tuesdays with Jonas Sickler
Description: Jonas Sickler with Jason Barnard about where do branded searches on Google come from?
Full Description:
Why do people search for brands on Google? Join us to explore the questions that drive us to make those searches, and what we expect to find. We’ll put search intent under a microscope and unravel the tangled threads of the customer journey as we examine the “why” behind branded searches.
Consumers bounce between online and offline channels as they ride the customer journey roller coaster. And they search company names for many different reasons at various points in the journey. For example, we search brands in Google when:
Comparing companies
Narrowing down products from a brand
Navigating to a website
Looking for directions to a store
Researching a CEO or company for investing
Reading product reviews
Leaving reviews
Looking for customer service information
Reading breaking news about a brand crisis
Looking for a job
Researching social or environmental impact of a company

Description: One of a Kind Fraud Risk Management Event
Full Description:
Growing Globalization, more competitive markets, and COVID-19 has accelerated the pace of digital transformation causing an increase in the demand for technological developments within organizations. This has led to an increase in the fraudulent practices, and have provided people intending to commit fraud with new scenarios and new methods to carry out these activities. Fraud and misconduct can seriously damage the reputation for integrity leading to decline in market confidence and public trust. It can also expose businesses to legal, regulatory, and reputational damage. Therefore, it is essential for businesses to take a strong and proactive stance against fraud and develop a robust mechanism to combating fraud and protect itself from increased vulnerability.
 
Integrating technological solution that can detect fraud at the very early stage and can prevent it from happening is the very crucial step that every businesses needs to take. Artificial Intelligence (AI), Biometrics & Big Data analytics are playing a critical role in fraud detection & prevention across various industries. It can also provide standardized processes that integrate large quantities of transactional data allowing to monitor, control, manage and optimize processes, ensuring revenue assurance and risk management in real time.
​
Business Fraud & Risk Management is a networking event that will invite visionary speakers and leaders from the fields of Business, Services, Innovation, Technology, and IT in order to address the challenges and opportunities associated with Fraud & Risk Management across industries.

Description: Web3 Community Gathering
Uszanowanko Programowanko #59: Powakacyjne PHP-owe opowieści
Full Description:
Wakacje już za nami, jesień coraz bliżej, a to oznacza jedno. Kolejny sezon Uszanowanka Programowanka! Na pierwszą powakacyjną edycję naszego wirtualnego meetupu zapraszamy do krainy PHP. Przed nami jak zwykle dwie prezentacje – w trakcie pierwszej z nich, Tomasz Surowiec opowie o “read modelach” i ich wykorzystaniu, zaletach oraz ewentualnych wadach. Druga prelekcja będzie natomiast poświęcona testowaniu API. Połączenie z bazą danych czy implementacja w pamięci? Które z podejść sprawdzi się lepiej? Po każdej prezentacji jak zwykle będziecie mogli zadawać pytania naszym uszanowankowym prelegentom. Widzimy się 28 września. Uszanowanko!
Program:
– Tomasz Surowiec, PHP Lead Developer – Jak skutecznie read model. Case study
Opowieść o tym, jak w projekcie legacy, który już ledwo dychał, udało się zaimplementować read model oparty na ElasticSearch (choć nie bez przeszkód i czasami pod prąd). Podczas prezentacji aplikacja legacy i walka o przyspieszenie zapytań posłuży jako punkt wyjścia do przeanalizowania konceptu “read modeli”. Po co wdrażamy je do aplikacji? Jakie są metody utrzymania ich w spójności? A w końcu – ich wady i zalety. W przypadku wspomnianej aplikacji zapytania które trwały około 8 minut udało się przyspieszyć do poniżej 1s (choć nie obyło się to bez potknięć). Zobacz jak!
– Krystian Żądło, PHP Developer – Testy API: połączenie z bazą danych czy implementacja w pamięci
Testy integracyjne wykonują realne żądania na API. Trzeba zatem zadbać o odpowiednie skonfigurowanie środowiska do testów. Kwestia danych to jedno z podstawowych zagadnień z którym należy sobie poradzić. Do tematu można podejść na kilka sposobów, ale sprowadzają się one do dwóch kategorii: baza danych albo implementacja w pamięci. Dowiedz się, które z nich sprawdzi się w twoim projekcie.

The Forum of Incident Response and Security Teams (FIRST) is an international not-for-profit organization bringing together a variety of security and incident response teams. Provide prompt rapid reaction to incidents

Event Name: Future of Tourism World Summit Barcelona 2021
Description: As the world faces a climate emergency, tourism must lead the way in adapting.
Full Description:
As the world faces a climate emergency, tourism must lead the way in adapting, becoming more sustainable and transitioning towards net-zero growth. At the same time, the sector must overcome the biggest challenge in its history. The COVID-19 pandemic brought international tourism to a near-complete standstill.
The sector must not only restart and recover, but it must also ensure future growth is more inclusive and responsible. Out of crisis can come opportunity. Clear, principled leadership will be required to realize tourism’s transformative potential.
Now is the time to build a better tourism:
FOR PEOPLE
Tourism can be a source of opportunity and empowerment. It must centre the needs of host communities and provide decent jobs for all, especially for youth, women and the most vulnerable groups in our societies. The tourism of the future must embrace local values, respect cultures and preserve and celebrate our unique and shared heritage, while at the same time adapting to digitalization and supporting new jobs skills.
The UNWTO Global Code of Ethics for Tourism, provides a framework against which tourism can develop and grow while always putting people first, while the UNWTO International Code for the Protection of Tourists makes clear the sector’s responsibilities to individuals, providing reassurance and restoring trust in travel.
FOR PLANET
Tourism must live up to its climate action responsibilities as a matter of urgency. All tourism stakeholders must assess and address tourism’s use of energy, land, water and food resources, as well as tourism-related carbón emissions. Now is the time to develop new models to reformulate and transform tourism and accelerate progress towards sustainability and net-zero growth, while providing innovative financing and the necessary investment infrastructure to make ambitious intentions a reality.
Measurement and disclosure of CO2 emissions in tourism also needs to be stepped up, accelerating decarbonisation advancing towards a sustainable tourism sector that advance the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) while remaining profitable.
FOR PROSPERITY
Tourism is a major pillar of economic growth and wellbeing, one of the world’s leading employers, and a leading generator of opportunity and empowerment. The sector must commit to safeguarding businesses and livelihoods. Destinations and companies should be supported in becoming more competitive by diversifying and building greater resilience through skills development, innovation and digital transformation.
Industry Group: Education, Information Technology, Sales and Marketing, Sustainability, Travel and Tourism
Industry: Education, Information Technology, Marketing, Sustainability, Tourism

Event Name: How International Image/Video Search Works - Kalicube Tuesdays with Heba Ashour (Bing)
Description: Heba Ashour talks with Jason Barnard about how international image/video search works.
Full Description:
There’s a famous saying that ‘A picture is worth a thousand words’. This is most relevant now to the domain of web search, where, in recent years, users everywhere are gravitating more towards consuming visual media for a quick and concise view of information. With this being a global phenomenon, it’s important that we enable users to find the information they’re seeking and that’s contextually relevant to them given any language they choose to express themselves in. In this talk, we’ll chat about what are key considerations for international image/video search, where language agnostic vs. language specific aspects help, and how deep learning is leveraged, more specifically how both text and media embeddings with vector-based search are used, to find the best image/video content to delight users. 
Additional reading
https://blogs.bing.com/search-quality-insights
Join Heba Ashour and Jason Barnard for this week’s episode of Kalicube Tuesdays!

In heavily regulated industries such as healthcare, digital innovation can be slow to progress. However, once organizations push towards digital transformation and innovation, benefits such as revenue growth, patient volume, and cost of care can take priority. Healthcare organizations are looking for an approach to cost-effective and technically efficient build-out to help on their digital transformation journeys. - Enables applications that support integrated care pathway management and holistic views of each patient
- Details on the healthcare-specific AI toolkit for building and running AI applications
- How supporting apps improve care coordination ,efficiency, and costs

Description: he Human Health Summit (HHS) will be an innovative and informative international meeting
Full Description:
INTRODUCTION
The outbreak of COVID-19 has sparked a discussion about the state of global health. The pandemic was an enormous shock for governments, NGOs, administrative agencies, businesses, and professionals. It has resulted in a long-lasting impact on health systems, economies and societies. It is urgent now more than ever, that we rethink our actions and formulate proposals to be better prepared for the future.
Human Health Summit - not just another virtual meeting
The Human Health Summit (HHS) will be an innovative and informative international meeting place to consider the course of future human health. Eminent academics and researchers, clinicians, public health professionals, health care specialists, economists, scientists, policy makers, social workers, students and other related professionals from a wide range of industry sectors will come together to share their knowledge and experience.
Summit and Beyond
HHS is a one-of-a-kind summit focused on building a World Integrated, Sustainable Health Eco-System (WISHES) and bringing it to life by developing concrete actions to progress after the event. International, multi-disciplinary working groups and taskforces will collaborate across six sectors: Health & Wellbeing, Knowledge & Education, Industry & Governments, Food & Poverty, Economy & Commerce, and Environment & Energy.

Welcome to the age of Big Data. With over 1.145 trillion MB of data created every day, go-to-market teams like yours have more information and resources at their fingertips than ever before. 
But in a world of so much data – and with the evolution and explosion of Artificial Intelligence transforming the way businesses use that data – how can you ensure the information you're collecting is fueling accurate, unbiased business insights? • What AI is (and is not), and the applications to the world of CRM 
• Why poor data is the top reason AI initiatives fail, and how to build a foundational data management process to get your CRM data in order
• The inherent risks of “data bias”, and how to establish a data governance program that not only meets ethical (and regulatory) standards, but also informs accurate, unbiased business insights

Full Description:
The “Trusted X LA Summit” is an exclusive gathering of top music, tech, and entertainment professionals to decode NFTs, blockchain, cryptocurrency, & web3.
We are proud to partner with Amber Group, Faculty Group, Opolis, SKALE Labs, Prager Metis, Axos Bank, Christie's, Family Office Association, Cointelegraph and more.
Cryptocurrency and NFTs have been a hot topic – and one that advisors with high net worth clients are looking for concrete guidance on. Many clients are heavily invested in the space, and are interested in creating and collecting NFTs. This has created a series of unique challenges from a tax, legal, and risk perspective. The slow roll-out of State and Federal legislation adds to the complexity.

They handle their clients’ complete picture: from their banking and bill pay, to insurance, cyber-security, business ventures, large purchases and investing.
“Over the past few years, having a few clients ‘dabbling’ in cryptocurrency has turned into a powerful set of tools for entertainers to generate revenue, and engage and grow their fan base. In many cases musicians generated more revenue from NFTs and investing in cryptocurrencies in the past two years than anything else,” says Matthew Hoffman, the founder of Trusted Advisor.

Managing Client Investments in Crypto / NFTs
Revenue Generation for Artists
Understanding Copyright, IP and Royalties
Tax Guidelines / Implications
Structuring Partnerships & Collaborations
Minting NFTs & Building Fan Engagement
Managing Risk & Protecting Digital Assets

The report shows more than 30% of invoices within the UK are not being paid within the agreed terms. Are you also battling a similar scenario of late payments, missed early discounts, or the risk of being non-compliant with statutory regulations – leading to damaged relationships with your suppliers? Not only that you lose out on better pricing negotiations as well adding costs to your business.
Added to this, organizations incur a significant cost to carry out the reporting itself and be compliant, somewhere to the tune of £40k in setup cost and £16k in annual reporting cost.

Description: How to continue delivering performance in a cookieless world
Full Description:
By the end of 2023, Google will be deprecating the 3rd party cookie from chrome, following other tech platforms in ushering in the privacy-first era. Following on from the removal of IDFA and GDPR, the end of cookies will change the way marketers are able to understand, reach, and engage their customers. This shift in relationship with personal data is going to mean an industry wide reset on how we market to the modern consumer.
In our latest webinar, we’ve partnered with The Trade Desk to take a look into the end of cookies – why it’s happening, what this means for marketers, and how you can continue delivering performance in this new data environment. We’ll be getting into the depths of what it will look like from a campaign level as well as exploring the solutions available for marketers.
Make sure to sign up today and secure your seat.

Description: Kim Krause Berg talks with Jason Barnard about how the better web accessibility improves profits.
Full Description:
Changing Web Accessibility Practices into Service to Others Opens New Opportunities for Business
Web accessibility has a terrible reputation. It’s viewed as too costly, too time consuming to learn and blamed for wrecked artistic creativity. To convince companies to build inclusive websites and mobile apps, nothing beats ill informed, fear-based tactics like ADA lawsuit threats. In a competitive market, inclusivity is the deal breaker. Human experience design communicates a commitment to diversity, equality, accessibility, and service to others.
Service to others? Yes. This is what will make your company different from the competition. You invest in truly understanding not only who uses your website or web app, but how they do it. This is not the same thing as why. Profits, conversions, brand reputation. None of that is news. What is going to turn your ship around is exploring how to improve human experience on the web for millions of people who are excluded because we have ignored how they use it

AI-Driven Drug Repurposing & Repositioning Summit

How Healx combines AI with drug discovery expertise to find novel treatments for the 95% of rare conditions that do not have an approved treatment.

Event Name: Uszanowanko Programowanko #58: Letnie lambdy i bujanie w chmurach nad Doliną Krzemową
Description: Uszanowanko Programowanko #58: Letnie lambdy i bujanie w chmurach nad Doliną Krzemową
Full Description:
Jak czerwiec to lato. Jak lato to chmury. Jak chmury to bazy danych. A do tego wszystkiego dodamy sobie stado lambd! Na ostatnie przedwakacyjne Uszanowanko zapraszamy w podróż po Dolinie Krzemowej. Z jednej strony – Mikołaj Glistak opowie o tym, jak działa Firestore, z drugiej – Bartosz Drozdz skupi się na skutecznym ogarnięciu lambd w taki sposób, by nie wymknęły się spod kontroli. Z obu prezentacji dowiecie się o dobrych praktykach i sztuczkach, dzięki którym stosowanie lambd i Firestore’a Was nie zaskoczy. Po każdej prezentacji jak zwykle będziecie mogli zadawać pytania naszym uszanowankowym prelegentom. Widzimy się 29 czerwca. Uszanowanko!
Program:
– Bartosz Drozd, Senior Node.js Developer – Jak utrzymać stado Lambd w ryzach – AWS, a w szczególności serverless computing, oferuje nam możliwość skalowania naszych systemów out-of-the-box. W większości przypadków jest to nam bardzo na rękę, ale… Co w sytuacji, gdy potrzebujemy z chirurgiczną precyzją kontrolować, ile aktualnie Lambd jest w użytku? Okazuje się, że nie jest to do końca taka prosta sprawa, gdyż AWS uporczywie robi wszystko, co może, aby wyskalować nasz system, niezależnie czy tego chcemy, czy nie. W tej prelekcji zaprezentuję możliwe sposoby rate limitingu naszych funkcji. Za przykład posłuży nam komunikacja z 3-rd party API, gdzie w większości przypadków jesteśmy ograniczeni ilością requestów, jakie możemy wykonać w jednostce czasu, żeby nie otrzymać 429-tki.
– Mikołaj Glistak, Node.js Developer – Firestore czyli ognista baza od giganta z Doliny Krzemowej – Podczas codziennej pracy każdy z nas korzysta z różnych baz danych,
Każda baza ma zachowania typowe dla siebie. Firestore to nierelacyjna baza od Google, która posiada wiele nietypowych funkcjonalności, wiele ciekawych rozwiązań. W tej prezentacji dowiemy się o paru fajnych zastosowań w Firestore i na co warto uważać przy implementacji tego rozwiązania.

Event Name: Managing the AI & ML Lifecycle: "ML Ops" and Beyond Training & Certification
Description: Managing the AI & ML Lifecycle
Full Description:
Developing AI and machine learning models is just the first step to keeping AI and ML systems performing and providing their needed value to the organization. In addition, organizations are realizing the need to manage models produced by other parts of their organization of third-parties. The developing area of Machine Learning Operations (ML Ops) and additional aspects of machine learning lifecycle management has emerged to address these needs. The Managing the AI & ML Lifecycle: "ML Ops" and Beyond course provides a foundational overview of AI & ML lifecycles, concepts around MLOps, deep dive into each of the aspects of AI & ML lifecycle management, details on ML Ops needs and capabilities, and provides a guidebook for managing ML projects as they continue to iterate, as well as steps and practical guidance for how to adopt an MLOps game plan at your organization to ensure success. This course provides a certification upon successful completion, has no prerequisites, and is appropriate for people with different roles and levels of expertise.
 
Total Training Hours: Twenty four (24) hours of instruction plus exercises
Minimum Enrollment: Through FY 2022, minimum enrollment is a group of 10 or more

The Practical & Comprehensive Ethical & Responsible AI Framework Development Training & Certification provides a comprehensive deep dive into the components of ethical & responsible AI frameworks and provides a guided, step by step approach for crafting an implementable Ethical and responsible AI framework. This course dives deep into a comprehensive ethical AI framework, which standardizes ethical frameworks from over 60 organizations including governmental, corporate, and leading organizations. Using this comprehensive framework, trainees will be able to understand the range of ethical and responsible AI & data needs across societal ethics, responsible use of AI, AI systemic transparency, governance of AI systems, and algorithmic interpretability and explainability. This course provides the "Quickstart" Cognilytica's Comprehensive Ethical AI Framework as well as additional support materials so that trainees can develop their own frameworks for AI and data projects. This course combines the best elements of ethical AI frameworks into a cohesive, well-defined set for buyers and builders of AI systems and is a great starting point for organizations looking to build their own AI framework. This course provides a certification in the Management of Ethical & Responsible AI Systems, has no prerequisites, and is appropriate for people with different roles and levels of expertise.

Event Name: Kalicube Tuesdays Monthly Roundtable: SEO and Knowledge Graph-based Chatbot
Description: In this webinar, Teodora Petkova, Beatrice Gamba and Jason Barnard will talk about SEO and knowledge graph-based chatbot.
Full Description:
Wordlift Monthly Roundtable (March 2022)
Or: A hitchhiker’s guide to Conversational AI
The conversational AI market, including chatbots and intelligent virtual assistants, is expected to grow at a CAGR of 22% during 2020–25, reaching almost US$14 billion by 2025 (source: Deloitte).
Yet, many of today’s AI assistants don’t use as much deep learning as we might think. While it’s common practice to apply machine learning to NLU (for intent detection), many implementations still use traditional rule-based or manual approaches that are tedious and time-consuming.
There are two areas of innovation in conversational AI where our SEO-minded approach can make a difference: training the agent with little manual effort and handling complex conversations by effectively re-using the content we already have on our websites.
During this webinar, Beatrice Gamba, SEO Strategist & Senior Digital Project Manager at WordLift, and Teodora Petkova, Experienced Semantic Content Writer, will deep dive – with the help of Jason Barnard – into Knowledge Graph-based Conversational AI. More practically, we will see how we can re-use FAQ-based content and increase the ability of the chatbot to understand a wide variety of inputs from the users. How do we write this content, and what else can be done with content knowledge graphs.
Organised by Kalicube in partnership with Wordlift.
Part of the Kalicube Tuesdays series.

After 2 years, IFGS finally returns to the historic Guildhall in the City of London, and will welcome the brightest and best from the FinTech ecosystem to discuss and debate the crucial issues facing the sector and beyond.
The UK continues to be a leader in financial innovation. Its place at the centre of global financial services, with supportive regulation, access to world-class talent, and a rich investment landscape has made it a hotbed of startups and established FinTechs. These new and exciting businesses are working to change and evolve the sector for the benefit of consumers and businesses alike. 
IFGS 2022 will convene industry leaders ranging from innovators, institutions, regulators to policy-makers, startups and investors to one place. The agenda will shine a spotlight on the global FinTech ecosystem, with an increased focus on the key areas that are enhancing, empowering and ensuring that FinTech and Financial Services are sustainable and inclusive to all.

Event Name: Adopting AI, ML, and automation in the banking industry with Agus Sudjianto, EVP, Head of Corporate Model Risk at Wells Fargo
Description: March 2022 Enterprise Data & AI Feature Presentation
Full Description:
The March 2022 Enterprise Data & AI featured guest speaker is Agus Sudjianto, Executive Vice President, Head of Corporate Model Risk at Wells Fargo and his presentation "Adopting AI, ML, and automation in the banking industry" Thursday, March 3, 2022 from 11:30 AM - 1 PM ET!
The banking industry has rapidly adopted Machine Learning for various applications for predictive analytics and process automation. The adoption of AI/ML is very natural because of the nature of the business that is both data and process intensive. While the benefits of AI/ML are very compelling, they are also bringing new risks beyond the traditional financial risk. With their model risk management practice that has been maturing in the last 10 years, banks are ahead of other industries in managing the risk of AI/ML. One of the key aspects to manage the risk is model explainability. 
While the adoption of so called ExplainableAI, which is typically ‘black box’ machine learning models accompanied by post-hoc explainability tools, is becoming more common for low risk applications, the concern remains for high risk areas such as credit underwriting; thus large banks are typically more cautious in adopting the methodology. There are many recent developments on inherently interpretable, self-explanatory machine learning models without the problem of post-hoc explainers. The focus of my talk will cover applications of AI/ML, their risk management as well as the approach for designing inherently interpretable machine learning for high-risk applications.
Be sure to stick around for Q&A at the end! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website: https://events.cognilytica.com/CLNTkxMnwxOA
Agenda:
11:30 - 12:30pm: Featured Presentation
12:30 - 1:00pm: Your Q&A and interaction
Industry Group: Artificial Intelligence, Data and Analytics, Financial Services, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Software
Industry: Artificial Intelligence, Big Data, Finance, Financial Services, Information Technology, Machine Learning

Description: Understanding of new technologies emerging for space medicine
Full Description: Understanding of new technologies emerging for space medicine will become ever-more important with the soon-to-come plunging of launch prices, enabling thousands of people, many not necessarily in the best of physical health, to visit space in the near future. In addition, with that much activity, the chances of accidents will vastly increase, and many of them will need to be dealt with in space, because waiting for an ambulance to get back to Earth may be too late. But we haven’t developed protocols or procedures for surgery or burn treatments in free fall (though ironically, that may be the best environment in which to treat a burn victim, and conceivably, there could even be orbital hospitals for such cases).
