Event Name: The Landscape of Cancer Vaccines and Research Platforms: The Cutting Edge
Description: Unique market study revealing R&D platforms for developing therapeutic cancer vaccines, the science behind the development.
Full Description:
Deep Pharma Intelligence held a virtual event (on November 23), which was a unique opportunity to share our findings from a unique market study revealing R&D platforms for developing therapeutic cancer vaccines, the key players in each category, the science behind the development, and case studies illustrating opportunities and challenges of each research strategy. 
​We presented our categorization of the 5 platforms — including relatively mainstream strategies — Neoantigen Platform, Tumor-associated Antigens Platform, Cellular Platform, and Oncolytic Viruses Platform — and the latest breakthrough and a potentially disruptive research strategy — Antigenic Essence Platform.

Description: Annual tent camp startup forum organized in seaside areas.
Full Description:
Sevan Startup Summit 2019
Seaside Startup Summit is an outdoor campsite-based global forum that fosters intensive deal-making and immersive conversations about the hottest current topics in entrepreneurship since 2016. The event attracts leading angels, VCs, entrepreneurs and policy makers willing to join their peers in an intimate setting to think, act and transform their environment via entrepreneurship.
During the 4 years of operations, Seaside Startup Summit (SSS) has gathered around 15,000 participants from all over the globe. So far the Summit was held in UAE, India and Armenia by gathering local and regional influencers and policy-makers. In UAE the summit became a flagship event for the MENA region and has become a unique platform for cooperation. The commitment of over 1,000,000$ was gained during the event. In India SSS emerged to the unique Indian startup culture and gathered entrepreneurs operating in dozens of fields, giving them a chance of cross-communication. 
The next event will be in Armenia from 28th of July to 3rd of August at the shore of lake Sevan. The regional flagship startup event of this summer includes a week-long international level micro-acceleration program supplemented by a series of workshops for qualified startups, introductory sessions for aspiring entrepreneurs, and dialogues with inspiring leaders. All the participants are living in the tents during the whole event, which ensures the non-formal part of the event.
In 2019 the summit programme is divided into two parts, a booster acceleration programme with international experts and and a starter programme focusing on idea and pre-seed startups. The combination of both ensure a maximum of targeted capacity development effectiveness and the opportunity to use international experience as knowledge source for joint learning.
This is a specially designed programme dedicated to aspiring entrepreneurs and idea-stage startups – with a focus on Armenian teams and startups. The programme features a series of talks that examine and explain key building blocks of the Business Model Canvas. Sevan Startup Summit 2019 is accepting applications for up to 80 qualified teams. Participants will be divided into Industry Tracks and will have access to leading Mentors and Industry Experts during the one-on-one mentorship, dialogue Session, Pitch Practice and specially designed workshops. Mentors will work with teams to sharpen their business and pitching skills and prepare for the Industry Track Battles. At the end of the programme, teams within each Industry Track will pitch their ideas to an esteemed jury of investors and experts for a chance to go on to the Starter Big Battle. The top team from each Industry Track will receive US$1,500 in prizes. Up to 18 teams will be selected for the Semi-Finals out of which 6 teams will go on to participate in the Starter Big Battle Finals. The finalists will compete for US$10,000 in prizes for the top 3 teams and in-kind prizes worth up to US$20,000.
The booster programme is a specially designed intensive micro acceleration programme for qualifying start-ups that have developed an early prototype and secured some form of angel funding. Booster Track will be facilitated by expert Speakers and supported by Mentors, who will deliver a hands-on intensive acceleration experience. Top teams will be eligible for prize fund of US $10K and optional investments up to US $50K per-team from specially designed Booster funds.
The 4th Annual Sevan Startup Summit 2019 will be held on the shores of Lake Sevan, Armenia from 28nd July to 4th August 2019. For everyone interested in taking part in Sevan Startup Summit 2019 as a startup, investor or a speaker, the application is available here: https://www.sss.am/attend/.
One week of camping, learning, meeting interesting people and winning is ahead. Don’t miss the chance to be into the entrepreneurial spirit of the region.

Description: Uszanowanko Programowanko #56: Dwa oblicza AWS
Full Description:
Kwietniowe Uszanowanko odbędzie się w klimacie AWS. A ponieważ, jak wiemy – kwiecień plecień to i my przygotowaliśmy niezły miszmasz i stawiamy na przedstawienie dwóch oblicz AWS. Aleksander Patschek opowie o tym jak przekształcić komponenty z Figmy do gotowej aplikacji przy pomocy AWS Amplify Studio, a Krzysztof Łoś skupi się w swojej prezentacji na implementacji procesów w chmurze przy użyciu AWS Step Functions. Po każdej prezentacji jak zwykle będziecie mogli zadawać pytania naszym uszanowankowym prelegentom. Widzimy się 27 kwietnia. 
Program:
– Aleksander Patschek, Senior Frontend Developer, Od Figmy do gotowej aplikacji bez linijki kodu – AWS Amplify Studio jest nowością od AWS’a, która pozwala połączyć komponenty Figma z bazą danych i wygenerować gotowy kod React. Czy to oznacza, że frontend deweloperzy przestaną być potrzebni? A może te narzędzie to tylko chwyt reklamowy? I czemu AWS zainteresował się narzędziami low-code/no-code. Na to wszystko Aleksander odpowie w swojej prezentacji. I pokaże na żywo jak przejść od Figmy do gotowej aplikacji.
– Krzysztof Łoś, Node.js Developer, Amazon Step Functions. Sposób na implementację procesów w chmurze – Zmęczony łańcuchowym (i wieloogniwowym) wywoływaniem AWS Lambd przez inne Lambdy? Śledzenie poszczególnych inwokacji od początkowej do końcowej Lambdy to droga przez mękę? I nawet AWS X-Ray tu nie wystarcza? Rozwiązaniem jest Amazon Step Function, czyli usługa AWS umożliwiająca łączenie poszczególnych kroków logicznych w proces, z jasnym dostępem do historii i szczegółów wywołań.

Full Description: The Adverse Childhood Experiences (ACE) study was instrumental in understanding the prevalence of exposure to abuse, neglect, violence, trauma, and other adverse experiences. This landmark study expanded how the field understands the impact of trauma, particularly related to increased potential for serious physical, emotional, and psychological problems, as well as engaging in health-risk behaviors. As awareness increased, related to the prevalence of ACEs and their long term impact, the value of trauma-informed care emerged.

Event Name: Kalicube Tuesdays Monthly Roundtable: Building a Knowledge Graph from a SERP
Description: Nik Ranger, David Riccitelli and Jason Barnard talks about building a knowledge graph from a SERP.
Full Description:
Wordlift Monthly Roundtable (February 2022)
The Semantic Web and Linked Data are here, and Google heavily relies on them to understand your content and rank it better. This means that alongside a content strategy publishers need a data strategy that translates into creating a Knowledge Graph made of related concepts and entities. The Knowledge Graph of a website is like its backbone, it provides structured data and connects all the content, sending clear signals to Google.
Creating a Knowledge Graph from scratch though can be painful and time consuming.
In this session we will show how we turn the SEO Experts most preferred tool, Google Sheets, into a Knowledge Graph creator by leveraging the WordLift Add-on for Google Sheets. We’ll show the 3-steps process that will take the performance data of any website and turn it into a list of entities to jump start a Knowledge Graph.

Full Description:
The South by Southwest (SXSW) Conference & Festivals celebrate the convergence of the interactive, film, and music industries.
SXSW streamlined event with 24 conference tracks covering a wide variety of topics as seen through the lens of entertainment, tech, and culture. The Interactive, Film, Music, and Comedy festivals promise to bring unparalleled opportunities to discover and connect.
Join March 10-19 in Austin, Texas for unparalleled discovery, networking, and inspiration at the 2017 SXSW Conference & Festivals in Austin, Texas! This year’s event includes expanded access for all badge types marking new opportunities for learning, networking, and discovery. Apply to participate in one of the many prestigious SXSW categories – Interactive Innovation Awards, Film Submissions, Showcase Applications, and more.
MARCH 10-18. The SXSW Conference provides an opportunity for global professionals at every level to participate, learn, and network. Featuring a variety of tracks that allow attendees to explore what’s next in the worlds of entertainment, culture, and technology, SXSW proves that the most unexpected discoveries happen when diverse topics and people come together. SXSW Conference speakers come from all over the globe. Across the various themes and trends at SXSW, Featured Speaker sessions present a snapshot of the most transformative ideas shaping future. 
SXSW Festivals run March 10-19 and offer a unique opportunity to explore the worlds of Interactive, Film, Music, and Comedy with parties, awards, screenings, and showcases :
- The SXSW Interactive Festival provides a variety of compelling evening networking experiences that complement the many learning opportunities at the SXSW Conference.
- The SXSW Film Festival celebrates raw innovation and emerging talent both behind and in front of the camera. Featuring provocative documentaries, comedies, genre standouts and more, the festival has become known for the high caliber and diversity of films presented, and for its smart, enthusiastic audiences.
- The SXSW Music Festival is one of the largest and most influential global music industry events of the year, taking place every March in Austin, Texas – the Live Music Capital of the World.
- Growing from a singular night’s celebration of comedy’s biggest names into a week-long whirlwind of a festival, SXSW Comedy presents uniquely diverse programming that highlights exceptional emerging and established talent.
SXSW plays host to many distinctly different exhibitions that connect people from all over the world.
- March 12–15. The Trade Show highlights the integrations and overlaps between SXSW’s converging industries, hosting a diverse range of forward-thinking exhibitors – from promising startups to established industry leaders.
- March 16–18. Drawing in developers, manufacturers, and fans from all facets of the community, the Gaming Expo is the epicenter of gaming culture at SXSW. Here is where you’ll find the Geek Stage, Esports Tournament Stage, Indie Corner, Tabletop Experience, Open Play Areas, and much more.
- March 11–12. SXSW continue to inspire and connect professionals from around the world with the SXSW Job Market. A convenient meeting spot for innovative thinkers and equally innovative companies, the Job Market enables these professionals to match their skills with 21st century, cutting-edge employers.
- March 16–18. Presented by the American Poster Institute (API), Flatstock will display the works of the world’s top gig poster artists. The show features posters of varying styles, colors and techniques for sale by the talented artists who created them.
- Spotlights highlight new technology companies within SXSW’s industry-specific programming tracks including SXSW Music and Startup Village®.
- Heading into its fifth season, the SouthBites® Trailer Park is excited to host the best roving restaurants from Texas and across the US! Each new year welcomes back noteworthy SouthBites alum but also showcases rising names in the ever-expanding food truck industry.
- March 10–12. SXSW Create, the hardware hacking and maker arm of SXSW, is at it again with more space, more fun, and even more hands-on excitement. From 3D printing to drones to biohacking and much more, this community event showcases the disruptive solutions that are shaping future.
- March 16-18. The first installment of the SXSW Marketplace brings together local Austin boutiques and hand-selected national/global brands to create a unique shopping experience at the epicenter of SXSW.
SXSW provides several different forums where registrants can meet and mingle from Meet Ups, multi-day Lounges and a variety of Parties. SXSW Events and Lounges provide opportunities to meet and network with other creatives from around the world while enjoying complimentary food and drinks. Meaningful, career-enhancing, one-on-one connections are one of the most valuable aspects of attending SXSW.

The AltFi Festival of Finance explores innovation in fintech, banking, and lending in the UK and across Europe.
Full Description:
The AltFi Festival of Finance is a two-day in-person extravaganza exploring innovation in fintech, banking, and lending in the UK and across Europe. 
After running the Festival of Finance virtually in 2020 and 2021, AltFi is excited to launch the Festival in-person for the very first time! 
Across the two days at the Park Plaza London Riverbank, we’ll explore the UK’s fintech and alternative finance sector, the European market and will cap off the event with the infamous AltFi After Hours party in central London. 
Each day’s full agenda will be available soon, but you can expect to hear from 50+ speakers from the most innovative finance companies in the UK and Europe.

Join us and explore a world of new business opportunities.

Event Name: AI in Government - Data is King: Let’s Talk About It with Figure Eight Federal
Location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Description: December 14, 2021 AI in Governemnt Presentation
Full Description:
Featured Guest Speakers:
•Vinay Malkani, Chief of Engineering at Figure Eight Federal
•Jack Hild, Team Member and National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) Hall of Famer
Data quality is of the utmost importance when it comes to actionable insights and model performance. In this presentation, Vinay Malkani, Figure Eight Federal's Chief of Engineering will discuss why quality data is critical, opportunities and challenges associated with data, and how to integrate multiple data sources to produce consistent, accurate, and useful information. Jack Hild, Team member and National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) Hall of Famer and Figure Eight Federal team member will then discuss where and how Figure Eight Federal fits into the NGA and it's data management vision.
Join us for this presentation around areas related to:
•Data Fusion
•Data Integrity
•Key Factors of Model Performance
•How the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA) is currently using their data and where Figure Eight Federal fits.
and be sure to stick around for Q&A with Vinay and Jack at the end. More information available at: https://events.cognilytica.com/CLNjA2N3wxOA

Event Name: Uszanowanko Programowanko #55: Co QA może i jak dev dopomoże
Description: Uszanowanko Programowanko #55: Co QA może i jak dev dopomoże
Full Description:
W marcu oddajemy głos kobietom w IT. Dwie Anie z The Software House – managerki zespołów Node.js oraz QA – zabiorą Was w podróż do świata QA i software developmentu. Możecie spodziewać się historii związanych z migracją dużych ilości użytkowników między systemami oraz o tym, co tak naprawdę może QA w projekcie. Wszystkie opowieści będą oparte na faktach! Po każdej prezentacji jak zwykle będziecie mogli zadawać pytania naszym uszanowankowym prelegentkom. Widzimy się 30 marca. Uszanowanko!
Program:
– Anna Skawińska, Node.js Team Manager, Zmigrujmy 30 tys. użytkowników ze starego systemu. Co może pójść nie tak? – Jednemu z naszych klientów pomagaliśmy niedawno zmigrować bazę użytkowników z systemu legacy do rozwijanej przez nas aplikacji. A ze względu na to, że była to aplikacja operująca na wrażliwych danych – bezpieczeństwo było dla nas najważniejsze! Co wzięliśmy pod uwagę? Co się nie udało? Na co trzeba uważać przy podobnych przedsięwzięciach? Wpadnijcie na prezentację – wszystkiego się dowiecie!
– Anna Kalemba, QA Team Manager, Co QA może i czego nie powinien się bać? – Jakie narzędzia pomagają w pracy QA? Co można zrobić, by jeszcze lepiej testować? Podczas prezentacji Ani dowiesz się kim tak naprawdę jest QA, jakie narzędzia może wykorzystywać w swojej pracy, a które z nich pozwalają na jeszcze lepsze podejście do testowania. Jak wpływa to na jeszcze lepszą jakość aplikacji? Cała historia będzie oparta na faktach, a to wszystko dzięki współpracy z developerami.

Meditation transforms your mind, transforming mind means giving you a new vision of seeing life
Full Description:
Meditation transforms your mind, transforming mind means giving you a new vision of seeing life. meditation helps you by encouraging and developing concentration, clarity, emotional positivity, and a calm seeing of the true nature of things. Meditation is not as simple it sees when we meditate we have to sit silently and stop everything which we are doing. A person can stop physically doing things but can't eliminate the stream of jumbled thoughts that may be crowding your mind, It's not so easy to overcome the stress you have in your daily life. Meditation means self-awareness and experiencing the subtle aspects of mindfulness. In meditation, you understand yourself in a better way. In meditation, we focus on a particular thing to gain awareness and attention on the mind.
Thousand of students come to Yoga Essence Rishikesh for learning meditation, they join our course "Meditation Teacher Training India". 
In this course we give them, practicing 20+ meditation & mindfulness techniques, help them to know the science behind meditation. Give you the clarity of the core principles of meditation. Meditation is all about experiencing the power of silence.

Description: Service weekend at Willoughby Rescue
Full Description:
Spend an hour, a day, or the entire weekend to help us get ready for our next Summer of camping. Your time and energy help grow and maintain the vision and legacy of Brian J. Stephens, who started this rescue effort!
COVID vaccination required. Negative COVID test required.
Camp with us, enjoy the campfire at night with old and new friends, and hang out with the farm animal rescues.
We have a number of projects that we need help with in addition to the annual spring clean-up around the grounds.
We will be building two new campsites (camping is a big income generator for the rescue). Plus there is painting of the greenhouse and the tent decks that volunteers built last year.
There are donkey hooves to trim, wood debris to be gathered, poop to shovel, and more!
No experience is necessary.
Pack your mask, sleeping bag if you want to spend the night, and commune with the critters! Boots and gloves are recommended (it can be muddy and poopy).
Plus last fall volunteers planted 2,500 daffodils and they should be in bloom this weekend!
Can't join us? Donate to help the herd. It costs about $10 a day to feed the rescues.

Description: Splunk's annual customer and developer conference
Promoting greater diversity and ethical sharing of genome data
Full Description:
Over the past few years advances in sequencing technology, efforts to mainstream genomics in healthcare systems, increased sharing of genomic information, and direct-to-consumer genetic testing have brought us to the cusp of the long-promised ‘genomics revolution’.
However, these advances have brought several challenges including the interpretation of results from genetic tests, which are in part amplified by the lack of standards and knowledge on outcomes from such results. In parallel access to direct-to-consumer personal genetic testing has whetted the public’s appetite for genotyping and ancestry testing, which can result in increased enquires with clinicians in public healthcare systems. Sharing personal genomic data could result in access by third parties for unintended purposes. Finally the vast majority of genomes in public databases continue to be of European ancestries, potentially exacerbating existing health disparities.
The second Personal Genomes conference aims to address these issues. It will bring together geneticists, bioinformaticians, and clinicians from academic and the commercial sector interested in learning the extent to which current genetic testing technologies can help people learn about their personal health and heritage. The meeting aims to democratise access to human genome technologies; facilitate and advocate best practice and governance of personal genomics data access; and promote openness and ethical sharing of personal genome data, while protecting privacy of the individuals.
Industry Group: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering
Industry: Biotechnology, Genetics, Health Care, Personal Health

CES is the world's largest tradeshow for consumer technology and America's largest annual tradeshow of any kind.
Full Description:
For 50 years, CES has been the launch pad for new innovation and technology that has changed the world. Held in Las Vegas every year, it is the world’s gathering place for all who thrive on the business of consumer technologies and where next-generation innovations are introduced to the marketplace.
The International Consumer Electronics Show (International CES) showcases more than 3,800 exhibiting companies, including manufacturers, developers and suppliers of consumer technology hardware, content, technology delivery systems and more; a conference program with more than 300 conference sessions and more than 160K attendees from 150 countries.
And because it is owned and produced by the Consumer Technology Association (CTA)™ — formerly the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)® — the technology trade association representing the $287 billion U.S. consumer technology industry, it attracts the world’s business leaders and pioneering thinkers to a forum where the industry’s most relevant issues are addressed.
The CES conference program is the place to go to take the pulse of the industry, learn about the latest trends and hear from top visionaries.

Event Name: Research Oral Presentation - Ruh - An Integrative Solution to Mindfulness for Muslims
Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Description: Oral Presentation at Yale University, at the 14th Annual Muslim Mental Health Conference, establishing an academic perspective of Ruh.
Full Description: The COVID-19 pandemic has reshaped the lives of many around the world. With an increased risk of isolation, anxiety and stress associated with public health measures, there has never been a greater demand for mindfulness training. Mindfulness training has been shown to reduce symptoms of subclinical depression, anxiety and stress, all while improving cognitive flexibility and immune functioning. Today, there are a host of mindfulness-based smartphone apps that are dedicated to improving the mental health and well-being of individuals. However, very few target Muslim populations who may be susceptible to poor mental health outcomes. This is largely due to Islamophobia, mental health stigma, and a lack of culturally competent and Islamically integrated mental health resources. Hence, the significance of Ruh, a mindfulness-based smartphone app based on the Islamic model of the Soul. It uses an inherently Islamic framework to integrate Islamic teachings with mindfulness techniques to promote positive mental health and well-being. With over 300 early access users, Ruh has provided a platform for its users to connect the mind, body and ruh (the soul) into one.

Event Name: Kalicube Tuesdays Monthly Roundtable: Making Multi-Modal Matter in SEO
Description: In this webinar, Andrea Volpini, Bill Slawski and Jason Barnard will talk about how to make multi-modal matter in SEO.
Full Description:
Wordlift Monthly Roundtable (January 2022)
Google is leveraging MUM to improve the customer journey across Search, Lens, and other surfaces. MUM is multi-modal and encompasses vision, auditory, and language understanding simultaneously.
Traditional AI models handle one modality of information at a time. They can take in text, images, or speech — but typically not all three at once as MUM does. BERT, for example, can analyse the co-occurrences of words within the same page and understand their context. MUM takes it to an entirely new level by reading terms in any language and by combining, for example, information in visual and tactile modalities.
This session will be a deep dive into entity-based content modeling, best practices for improving rankings on Google Lens, and an overview of how the latest research advances are being implemented on Google Search.

Event Name: Prepping your CRM for AI: Why AI Initiatives Fail & How to Lay the Foundation for Data Success
Description: February 10, 2022 Enterprise Data & AI Event
Full Description:
Enterprise Data & AI is hosting guest speaker Guy Hanson, Vice President, Customer Engagement (International) at Validity Inc. and his presentation "Prepping your CRM for AI: Why AI Initiatives Fail & How to Lay the Foundation for Data Success" Thursday, February 10, 2022 at 12 PM - 1 PM ET!
 
Welcome to the age of Big Data. With over 1.145 trillion MB of data created every day, go-to-market teams like yours have more information and resources at their fingertips than ever before. 
But in a world of so much data – and with the evolution and explosion of Artificial Intelligence transforming the way businesses use that data – how can you ensure the information you're collecting is fueling accurate, unbiased business insights? And what steps can you take – today – to improve your organization’s CRM data management processes to prepare for the future of AI and set your go-to-market teams up for success? 
TUNE IN LIVE on Thursday, February 10th at 12:00pm ET to hear from Guy Hanson, Vice President of Customer Engagement at Validity, as he breaks down the current state of CRM Data Quality and outlines the strategies you need to stay ahead. You will learn: 
• What AI is (and is not), and the applications to the world of CRM 
• Why poor data is the top reason AI initiatives fail, and how to build a foundational data management process to get your CRM data in order
• The inherent risks of “data bias”, and how to establish a data governance program that not only meets ethical (and regulatory) standards, but also informs accurate, unbiased business insights
Be sure to stick around for Q&A at the end! Register and attend for free on the Cognilytica event website: https://events.cognilytica.com/CLNjI5N3wxOA

Description: Financial Times | What's Next for America's Energy Transformation?
Full Description:
Soaring energy prices and the specter of energy shortages in recent times, amplified by the current Russia-Ukraine conflict, have been stark reminders that the road to cleaner energy is far from smooth. The FT Energy Source Live summit will take a deep dive into the issues set to reshape the US energy industry in the years ahead, and ask what's next for America’s energy transformation.
Join industry CEOs, thought leaders, energy innovators, policymakers, investors and our world-class FT journalists to hear their expert insights. On a series of panels and roundtable discussions, they’ll look at the implications of Russia-Ukraine tensions for the energy industry, the future of US shale and LNG, tackling the methane challenge, how oil and gas pipelines will adapt to a lower-carbon world, before examining alternatives and opportunities in powering the US’s future in new energy industries from offshore wind to new nuclear and the rapidly transforming US midstream. Above all, they’ll ask whether the US can lead in the burgeoning new energy markets of the future.

Event Name: Kalicube Tuesdays with Joseph J. Sherman and Jason Barnard: Effective Media Cadence for PR
Description: Joseph J. Sherman talks with Jason Barnard about effective media cadence for PR.
Full Description:
Joseph J. Sherman talks to Jason Barnard about building an effective public relations strategy that delivers results while focusing on people.
In this episode, Joseph J. Sherman shares his approach for engaging with editors, journalists, and bloggers.
– First, qualify media leads from marketing campaigns as sales opportunities. This means they must be treated with the appropriate respect, diligence, and urgent needs as they would with a sales lead.
– Contact potential media prospects through cold calls and emails that get responses.
– Build long-term trusting relationships with media professionals just as you would with prospects and clients.
– Proactively seek new media opportunities in a similar way that the company would pursue new business opportunities.
Set up meetings or calls between journalists, bloggers, and key team members in a similar way that you arrange meetings with prospective clients and sales executives.

Description: The first non-formal startup event in the region, and the first startup tent camp in the world.
Event Type: Competition, Conference, Demo Day, Expo, Hackathon, Meetup, Networking
Full Description:
Sevan Startup Summit: The first non-formal startup event in the region, and the first startup tent camp in the world. The event was organized by the Startup Armenia Foundation in summer of 2016, at Lake Sevan. The closing ceremony of Sevan Startup Summit 2017 was on 30th of July. During the 7 days of the Summit, the participants shared mode of life in the shore of Lake Sevan in tents. The organizers hosted more than 1000 participants and guests. Among them, there were 100 startup and software developer teams, mentors, lecturers, speakers, successful representatives of business field, journalists and many other people. The prize fund exceeded the determined $40,000 and reached $50,000.
Besides, of the money prizes the participants of the Summit got a unique chance to talk and connect with many successful startuppers and businessman. This year besides the invited professors and lecturers, who were holding the workshops, the Summit has a special format CampFire Talks, where the businessperson were telling their success stories. The talks were held around the campfire. The talks in this format have an aim to give the participants a chance to talk to the people who can play a big role in the future of their startups and help them to develop.
During the 3 competition days there were held 7 battles. Thanks to the general supporter of the Summit Beeline Armenia, it become possible to held a Campathon, a 24-hour coding event for the software developers.
The general partner of the Summit Ameriabank rewarded the Grand Prize of $8,000 to the winner of the Big Battle. The winner ANIX promised not to despair the ones who believed in their startup. The aim of the ANIX is to deliver a better customer service. To recall, the winners of all of the battles were decided by the jury, who were the successful representatives of the startups or businesses operating in certain fields.

Description: CONNECTS annual speaker series focuses on promoting awareness of social issues affecting our world through influential speakers.
Full Description:
CONNECTS annual speaker series focuses on promoting awareness of social issues affecting our world through influential speakers.
Every autumn we invite clientele and a variety of special guests to our speaker series, where outstanding thought leaders enlighten our hearts and minds with intuitive perspective.
WHY CONNECTS?
The idea was conceived after 9/11, when logical debate became difficult. Issues require conversation, and the media was not facilitating it. Do not get us wrong; we are not interested in pointless confrontation, but rather considering alternative points of views on subjects that matter.
Throughout our travels, we come across amazing people. We are always searching the globe for insight and inspiration, and have had transformative experiences in places such as Singularity University. Our community should benefit from our new insights in more ways than just smarter investments.
At our inception in 2004, we created CONNECTS, a speaker series to help inspire and motivate each of you to become increasingly involved in social issues that affect our world. A connection is the foundation of human existence; CONNECTS is just one way that we unite our community, locally and globally.

Event Name: Kalicube Tuesdays with David Amerland and Jason Barnard: Searcher Behaviour, Intent & Expectations
Description: David Amerland talks with Jason Barnard about searcher behaviour, intent and expectations.
Full Description: Google is implementing a number of different AI systems in an attempt to integrate knowledge graphs at the point of the search query. Despite that search appears to be less responsive and less accurate than it was five years ago. There is a real reason for this and it is linked to human behavior and it affects both marketers and content creators. David and Jason will discuss the question: why is search underperforming even as its computational power is increasing? David will then provide some of the solutions that can be applied here to ensure that from an SEO-point of view a business continues to be visible. To do so he will draw from the latest research in AI, Google’s implementation of MUM and BERT and the neuroscience that helps us better understand human behavior, especially when it comes to making purchase decisions.

The Uplive x Hekka Fashion New York Fashion Week 2022 Runway Show is a collaboration between Asia Innovations Group’s Uplive live streaming service and Hekka Fashion, an e-commerce platform.
The event will give up-and-coming designers the chance to show off their latest creations in one of the fashion industry’s most prestigious venues. The goal of the event is to demonstrate the future of fashion by bringing together performers, designers, and models from all walks of life.
Date: Tuesday, February 15th, 2022
Time: 8 PM (EST)
Place: Moonlight Studios – 330 Hudson St. New York, NY, 10013
Uplive will broadcast the New York Fashion Week Talent Award ceremony live on its mobile app as part of the event. All guests will be encouraged to show off their unique style and compete for prizes including cash, New York Fashion Week experience passes, the chance to perform on the runway, and many more to be announced.
The collection was inspired by the world’s post-pandemic reopening to travel and newfound passion for exploring the world. It featured activewear, flowy cocktail dresses, leisure, and vacation styles, all celebrating comfort, elegance, and femininity. Keppi (IG:@keppi.fitness), an emerging fitness brand partnered with Uplive and Hekka(IG:@hekkaofficial), debuted its activewear at the NYFW and handled giveaway prizes. Keppi is one of the rising brands on Hekkamall that had successful product launches.

Event Name: Make your event a success: How to make event photography pay for itself
Description: Presentation to discuss the importance of professional event photography
Full Description:
The importance of event photography for a successful event.
To be a success, any event needs proper promotion. And proper promotion relies on creating outstanding visual content. And, just as important, it needs to give you great ROI.
This event is about the importance of using professional event photography with your event, how to maximise its use, getting the most from your all visual content, and achieving your primary goal – creating a success!
We will be covering the need for - and implementation of - professional event photography and videography during all 3 stages of event organisation: pre-event, during your event and post-event.
